result.formatted_address: Shop 1, G/F, The Oakhill,16 Wood Road, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: Takumi by Daisuke Mori

reviews.text:
Masterfully prepared French Style Dishes, heavily Japanese influenced with European and japanese technics and  ingredients, by Daisuke Mori
great selection of Wines to acompany the Food

Food: above average
Service: average for such a price point (hkd 2k per pax without alcohol)
Ambiance: this is where I struggle.
1) the room is 12 seater, so you can notice everything. The room AC was replaced by a bix auxiliary AC adding 60 decibels to the dining room. The wine in the glasses was at 25 degres in 10mins (so no need to bring good wine there that would be a waste given the 27 degres in the restaurant)
2) re ordering bread: we were told no more bread so we got sliced toasts (from 7 eleven?). 1 star Michelin, really?
3) the deco, the smell (maybe due to the heat) need some serious revamping. Somehow it doesn t feel like you are in a fine dining place (plastic electric plugs added on to the wall, tons of small things that make it look low-end)
4) interaction with the chef. In a 12 seater L shape counter you could expect some interaction. We got none. Then why have a counter instead of normal tables?
So overall very mixed feeling. It has somewhat the potential on the food but we need some serious best practixes from other michelin starred restaurants.

Impressive.  Multi course teppanyaki in kaiseki style: seasonal imported ingredients, layers of complementary and contrasting flavor and attention to presentation.  Recommend the Uni supplement.  The setting isn't the most elegant or comfortable (cramped, lighting is a bit bright etc.) so it's not a place to linger but the food makes it well worth the trip.
Michelin 1 star restaurant. Japanese~French fusion cuisine. Excellent.
Food is good! Mori San is very focused when he is working, but after work is very sincere.
